divs: Sighting Details1. I was in my boyfriend's backyard near Martinsburg, West Virginia. I was taking pictures of the sky simply because it was a very beautiful blue. I had also been taking pictures of birds that were flying by. 2. I didn't see the object with my eyes but, when I uploaded the pictures I took, I realized that there was some weird object in one of the pictures. 3. When I first saw the object in the photograph I thought that it could possibly be a bird. However, there aren't any white birds in this area (except seagulls and I never saw a seagull) and the birds that were flying around the area around that time were plainly black and turning up as such in my other photos. I knew the object could not be a plane because I distinctly remember that there were no planes in the sky when I took the particular photo with the UFO in it. 4. I'm not sure what the object was doing because I didn't see it myself until I saw the picture. 5. I am curious about what turned up in the photograph I took. It may not be something out of the ordinary but I can't seem to think of what it could be because of the odd shape and bright coloration of the object. 6. I never gained or lost sight because I never saw it. For those interested, I posted the picture as an attachment. The object is on the right side of the photograph. The picture was not altered in any way before I attached it.
Summary: ufo in picture; didn't see myself but it turned up in a photo i took of the sky
